01:00:25.960 --> 01:00:27.970
As you rightly
mentioned, there's

01:00:27.970 --> 01:00:31.980
only so much-- each tool
has a range, you mentioned.

01:00:31.980 --> 01:00:37.250
So when you exhaust the tools
that can deal with matter,

01:00:37.250 --> 01:00:41.360
it doesn't mean that there's
not another reality besides that

01:00:41.360 --> 01:00:43.950
so how do you understand that?

01:00:43.950 --> 01:00:47.895
MARCELO GLEISER: So
the way-- the sort

01:00:47.895 --> 01:00:49.840
of typical response
to that is something

01:00:49.840 --> 01:00:51.370
called the binding problem.

01:00:51.370 --> 01:00:53.110
And the binding problem
is the following.

01:00:53.110 --> 01:00:55.650
If the brain is matter, right?

01:00:55.650 --> 01:00:59.360
And something else out there,
call it whatever you want,

01:00:59.360 --> 01:01:00.570
right?

01:01:00.570 --> 01:01:03.210
And as this something
else interacts

01:01:03.210 --> 01:01:05.960
with the matter
of the brain, that

01:01:05.960 --> 01:01:09.250
means it's exchanging some
kind of energy and momentum

01:01:09.250 --> 01:01:10.935
or something, which
is really physical.

01:01:12.030 --> 01:01:14.902
And so you should be
able to measure that.

01:01:14.902 --> 01:01:16.360
And the binding
problem is that you

01:01:16.360 --> 01:01:20.820
don't know how to bind this
immaterial with the material

01:01:20.820 --> 01:01:23.490
without producing some effect,
which is a physical affect.

01:01:25.370 --> 01:01:26.980
And so this is a
fundamental problem.

01:01:26.980 --> 01:01:32.600
So you can believe things
like that as an assumption,

01:01:32.600 --> 01:01:35.140
but it would be very hard to
verify this scientifically.

01:01:35.140 --> 01:01:36.515
So from a scientific
perspective,

01:01:36.515 --> 01:01:39.390
we go, I don't know. right?

01:01:39.390 --> 01:01:41.010
I mean, I hope not.

01:01:41.010 --> 01:01:45.280
I hope it's really all matter,
and matter is awesome already.

01:01:45.280 --> 01:01:46.950
Look at what it does, right?

01:01:46.950 --> 01:01:50.520
I mean, and the fact that
it's such a complex problem,

01:01:50.520 --> 01:01:54.230
the emergence of consciousness,
doesn't mean that may be

01:01:54.230 --> 01:01:58.480
unsolvable, doesn't mean that it
needs to be explained by other

01:01:58.480 --> 01:02:00.650
means that cannot be
verified scientifically.

01:02:00.650 --> 01:02:01.150
You know?

01:02:01.150 --> 01:02:05.970
Unless you're kind of
integrating in your mind

01:02:05.970 --> 01:02:08.100
other ways of knowing,
which is fine.

01:02:08.100 --> 01:02:09.210
I mean, people do that.

01:02:09.210 --> 01:02:11.254
I'm not Richard Dawkins here.

01:02:11.254 --> 01:02:12.920
You know, I'm a
[INAUDIBLE] kind of guy.

01:02:14.230 --> 01:02:16.040
And I'm totally
OK with that, but

01:02:16.040 --> 01:02:19.407
from a scientific perspective
it's very hard to justify that.

